HEADWORD: Perry
<hw>Per"ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>per⟦eacute⟧</ets>, F. <ets>poir⟦eacute⟧</ets>, fr. <ets>poire</ets> a pear, L. <ets>pirum</ets>. See <er>Pear</er> the fruit.]</ety> <def>A fermented liquor made from pears; pear cider.</def>  <rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

